			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My normal method of 'soloing' is to hydra in HoH.  I aggro kite with a druid, casting mostly snare with an occasional DoT thrown in (snare generates significantly more aggro than any DoT and costs less mana than you regen during the casting time).  I generally kite in one of the basements and cast 1-2 snares per run along the wall.  I send the pet immediately upon pulling, malosini, and then cast approximately 4-5 BoT and some number of free nukes per mob.  This is with Servant of Marr, 2 Blades of the Kedge, BOV, and a muzzle.  Average kill time is 2.75 minutes (including pull time) per mob.
<br />

<br />
Prior to Tuesday, I have never - in the 150+ AAs I have done in this manner - had the pet draw aggro.  Neither has my mage ever drawn aggro.  In fact, I have tested in the past *trying* to pull aggro off the druid by chain casting BoT as fast as I could.  It was impossible.
<br />

<br />
On Tuesday, the aggro rules changed noticably.  Even chain casting snare, I have to periodically back the pet off for 10-20 seconds, and I have to be extremely careful not to draw aggro on my mage.  I have pulled a mob onto myself on the second bolt after landing 10+ snares and a Swarming Death on the mob.  Prior to Tuesday, I could have exhausted my entire mana pool on the mob, and it wouldn't have blinked at me.
<br />

<br />
This isn't a big deal to me (except on Sentries and other unsnarables, who have become significantly harder because you have to get distance between snare attempts and thus can't chain it effectively) and has little or no effect on my experience gain, but it is very noticable.  It is *not* patch hysteria.  I keep very careful notes on my nuke frequency, fight durations, and exp gain (I have no time to waste gaining sub-optimal experience), and the change is evident from the data.
<br />

<br />
What was the change?  Has nuke aggro been increased (pets nuke too)?  Has snare aggro been reduced?  I somehow don't think it has anything to do with range, since I always bolt from point-blank range as the mob is passing me.  Is aggro just buggy?  I don't know.  I just know that in this particular circumstance, something has changed.
<br />

<br />
I should note that I have noticed absolutely nothing whatsover different on raids, excepting Rampage, which just seems bugged to all Hell.<br />_________________<br />Sage Utuno Myramar, Familjen</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
