			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is no question that there is "increased aggro", now.
<br />

<br />
In experience groups where I have as a benchmark months of camping and hunting in the same spots, I am drawing considerably, significantly more aggro than I did before.
<br />

<br />
It's very disheartening, as it was the "New DPS" that made the class more attractive once again.
<br />

<br />
Now, with the only means available to reduce aggro being to delay nuking longer, my DPS has been crippled.  
<br />

<br />
I use the word "crippled" deliberately.  <span style="font-weight: bold">This is a significant change.</span>
<br />

<br />
The lack of Mage solo-ability in PoP I was able to stomach with the idea that our higher DPS more than made up the difference in fun-factor for the Mage no longer being able to solo in the fashion he once did.
<br />

<br />
However, with this new aggro change, given that it is working as intended and won't change, the Mage's damage output is now lower, the irritation factor in XP groups higher (pong or longer kill times)  the "wow" factor of the Mage heading is back to the Kunarkian nerf basement.
<br />

<br />
Extremely annoyed and frustrated by this.
<br />

<br />
Gnomer</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
